50|$|The {{purpose of}} <b>tax-exempt</b> <b>bonds,</b> or private {{activity}} bonds, {{is to promote}} job creation and increase economic development in local areas; therefore, they {{are not limited to}} housing creation. These bonds are issued by state Housing Finance Agencies (similar to LIHTCs) or by local government development agencies. Since the interest on the bonds is exempt from state and local taxes, lenders who purchase the bonds pass on this savings onto borrowers through lower interest rates. <b>Tax-exempt</b> <b>bonds</b> are similar to conventional loans in that the borrower must pay back the principle plus interest to the lender; however, <b>tax-exempt</b> <b>bonds</b> typically have longer financing periods compared to conventional loans. In general, this type of bonding is utilized for projects over one million dollars.|$|R
