50|$|The Stimley-Blue Ridge Library of the Houston Public Library {{is located}} at 7007 West Fuqua in Blue Ridge. In 1997 the library was named after Sherman Stimley, the first African-American law {{associate}} of the firm Vinson & Elkins. In 1985 Stimley started the first consulting company exclusively dealing with <b>tax-exempt</b> <b>bond</b> law that was headed by an African-American in Houston.|$|E
